REQUIREMENTS
============
- if mysqlclient throws "OSError: mysql_config not found", run "sudo apt-get install libmysqlclient-dev"


DATABASE SETTINGS
=================
sudo mysql -u root
CREATE DATABASE ii20;
CREATE USER 'pazhitnov'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED by 'managing ii20 multimedia analytics';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON ii20.* TO 'pazhitnov'@'localhost';
- Run the db_superuser script (once) to set up your database superuser on Django's side.


SECRET KEY
==========
- For security reasons, not included with the repo.
- Run the generate_secret_key.py script (just once!) to set up your secret key


DATA
====
mkdir tetris/tetris_app/data
mkdir tetris/tetris_app/staticfiles/tetris/data
> Symbolic link your dataset(s) in BOTH those directories

USERS
=====
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser
> Username: pazhitnov
> Email address: <your address>
> Password: managing tetris for multimedia analytics

UBUNTU PACKAGES
===============
sudo apt install virtualenv mysql-server libmysqlclient-dev default-libmysqlclient-dev python3-dev nginx supervisor

VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
===================
virtualenv -p python3 env_tetris

SERVER
======
147.32.69.18

FIREWALL - PORTS
================
sudo ufw allow ssh
sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw allow http
sudo ufw allow https
sudo ufw allow 8000/tcp

USER
====
sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash mmtetris
sudo passwd mmtetris
<enter the password: "user making mm tetris happen">

GUNICORN CONFIG
===============
sudo mkdir /var/log/mmtetris
sudo chown mmtetris /var/log/mmtetris

SYSTEMD CONFIG
==============
sudo cp /home/mmtetris/sw/tetris/tetris_app/config/systemd/tetris.service /etc/systemd/system
sudo systemctl start tetris
sudo systemctl enable tetris

NGINX
=====
sudo ln -s /home/mmtetris/sw/tetris/tetris_app/config/nginx/tetris /etc/nginx/sites-enabled

LOGGING
=======
Ensure you have logrotate (default on Ubuntu), if not, install it.
sudo cp /home/mmtetris/sw/tetris/tetris_app/config/logrotate/mmtetris /etc/logrotate.d

NPM
===
npm i webpack webpack-cli --save-dev
npm i @babel/core babel-loader @babel/preset-env @babel/preset-react --save-dev
npm i react react-dom --save-dev